	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 8th 12:18 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>this is my experiance as a barbarian shaman on brell serelis. <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;             levels 1 - 7 can be soloed in everfrost. at level 5 start killing gnolls outside BB, and save polar bear pelts (<br>               the white ones ) and sell them to people in everfrost doing polar bear cloak quest, or give it to the female<br>               merchant in macs kilts at halas for raw-hide armor and exp. from 7 - 9, group in black burrow, by now you<br>               should be useing a craked staff. at level 9 you get sow, possibly the most usefull spell in the game, which<br>               you can sell to people around the area and make good cash, at this time you should eithor get a bloodforge<br>               hammer for around 10p, or if youre rich, you can get a cold iron morning star from some high level farmers<br>               in permafrost for around 30-50p. at this time, go to wisp isle ( eruds crossing ). to get there take the boat<br>               from south qeynos. kill the wisps and snakes, they are great loot and exp. you can take the greaters<br>               lightstone to gypsies in north karana for exelent exp, and they give you a book that sells for 8p, or if youre<br>               lazy you can sell the greater lightstones for 7p. here you can get real rich, save for banded armor and a 1<br>               handed magic weapon if you dont have alredy, aslo get jasper earings and rings. at around 15 solo in tundra<br>               till 16. at 16, you can go to highpass hold for great loot and exp, or solo the oasis for great exp, no loot<br>               though =(. if you are luckey enough to win stuff in highpass, go for a charred gaurdian sheild, 10ac 9wis. at<br>               this time i was useing an enameld black mace, 8/28 magic, and a CGS. stay at highpass till 19 then go back<br>               to halas to buy spells and souch. thats the end of part 1 for me. <br><br>----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>PART 2<br><br><br>               shaman strategy part 2<br>                                                                        By: Thorg<br>                                                                          7 posts<br>               Posted @ Wed, Aug 23rd 8:23 PM<br>                                                                   Score: Good[4.14]<br>               ok im taking this from level 19 where i left off.... <br><br>               19 spells are decent, affliction does about 180 damage, but in 2 min. healing is good to. at 19, i did the<br>               langseax of the wolves quest for a long while, its exelent cash if youre on a newer server, when i did it<br>               langseaxes sold for 25p and LoWs sold for 500p, thats how i got a lot of equipment. but for leveling i went to<br>               lake rathe and south karana and solo'd avaiks till 24. if you perfer to group go to high hold keep from 22-35.<br>               the 24 spells are exelent, new dd, a great dot. at 25 i began soloing tesch mas gnolls outside split paw (<br>               some difficulty at first but then i got the hang of it ) also to do this you should have around 150 wis because<br>               they have much much hp.what i did was cast envenemed breath, affliction, then root the gnoll and med until<br>               it brakes, then run far and cast DD, and envenemd breath again when it wore off till he was dead. Gnolls are<br>               GREAT exp solo and EXELENT loot. around 25 is when you should start totemic quests, although i use no<br>               totemic except the helmut because none of the other adds wisdom ( i used the totemic boots till 45 though<br>               when i got e-boots ).also, at 25 look for a spear and work on peirce (it comes in handly later). save for a<br>               jade chokadi prod, they cost around 800p on my server. also at level 25 i had the following equipment:<br>               blackend iron medallion, gold jasper earings, runed circulet, platinum jasper rings, platinum armband, cloak<br>               of the icebear, bloodstained tunic, totemic boots, gatorscale legs, splitpaw hide gloves, chiped bone bracers,<br>               enameld black mace, charred gaurdian sheild. stay soling gnolls for a while, you will get lots of cash. at 29<br>               you get healing upgrade, decent buffs, and invis. invis is great, i used it to get to alchemist room in<br>               permafrost and camp it forever to get many mammoth cloaks. at 29 it can be very dangerous, so take a<br>               friend to be safe ( wish i did ) just to break spawn or something, if its broken well you can solo it, just keep<br>               buffs up, and regen. i got 2 cloaks at 29, one to use and one i traded for a tesch val sinich ( 9/33 4wis 4int 40<br>               range effect poison ). at 34, you get........ A PET!!!!!!!!!! yes a pet! you get a NEW DD, and you also get<br>               GREAT buffs, 34 is heaven for shaman, you can solo gnolls with 1 bub of mana! at 35, i went to the bard and<br>               killed him, although i wish i hadden because when i forget to invis in qeynos i get mobbed. at 35 i went to<br>               lower guk at 35 and soloed for a bit. this is when i started grouping a lot, in the bedroom in lower guk, i got<br>               out of 35 in 10 hours! its extremly good exp in lower guk, i made a level a day from 35-38 in there! <br>               at 39, spells are exelent to, venem of snake, scourge, talisman of altune, new pet, more buffs. <br>               ok time for another equipment rundown, by now you should probably have a totemic helmut, they cost a lot<br>               or you can do the quest, a jade chokadi prod ( 11/33 6wis peirce ) get one of those new belts from paw that<br>               adds wisdom, but i had saved up and got a flayed turmoilskin belt. look for some forest loops also. at 39 if<br>               you want to solo do trolls in rathe mountains for nice safe exp, decent loot also. if you perfer to group to to<br>               executioners roon in lower guk, exelent exp and loot again. at 40, i went to frenzy room for exelent exp,<br>               good loot in there but its rare ( flowing black silk sash ). the 44 spells are good, new dd, new pet (this pet is<br>               wimpy though) and buffs. at 45 go to solesk b and stay in the window for 15 hours untill you level hehe. at 46<br>               if you want to solo go to specters in ferrot, or trolls in rathe mountains, but i was liking guk very much at this<br>               point so i stayed there. from 46-49 switch between frenzy and lord room, you can do exe room from 46-48<br>               but not much exp. at 47 exp it better in lord than frenxy room, but frenxy is MUCH safer. if you are luckey<br>               you will get a FBSS or SMR to trade for e-boots to. the 49 spells KICK SERIOUS ASS! you get e-bolt, a pet<br>               that hits for 51 damage, exelent buffs! so right now i am level 49, i solo ice giants now, to do that make pet,<br>               buff it up, alacraty pet, togor ice giant, root giant, e-bolt giant, plague giant, and heal pet and re e-bolt when<br>               you need, safe, great exp, and they drop about 10 to 50p ( in pp ) with gold and islver and copper each time.<br>               when igs are camped go farm permafrost anf get rich heh, thats my guide hope you liked it! if you see me on<br>               brell ill be glad to help out, remember wisdom is the most important stat for shamen! <br>----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>*ATTENTION*  i posted this origonally a few months ago, and in that time i have found something that a shaman should begin saving for ASAP.......<br><br>a JAUNDICED BONE BRACER!!! this thing is excellent! at 45, it casts a 263 DD for NO MANA! i can solo blues useing only 1/2 bub mana!  anyways, that concludes my shammy guide! hunt well!!!!<br><br>&nbsp;<br>†°•=THORG‡FROSTFIST=•°†<br>52nd season shaman<br>Brell Serilis<br>Grand Master Drunk</td></tr>
